00:34:23,600 --> 00:34:27,870
[Hyeyeon: probably aren't hitting it off
as well as we are.]

680
00:34:27,340 --> 00:34:28,340
I'm honestly...

681
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:30,270
[Heejin: Once we get there, you'll
probably talk to other people too, right?]

682
00:34:30,270 --> 00:34:31,600
[Hyeyeon: Exactly. Once we get there,]

683
00:34:31,600 --> 00:34:34,270
[Hyeyeon: I'll probably be chatting
with someone else in a second.]

684
00:34:34,270 --> 00:34:37,739
[Hyeyeon: But no one could possibly
click as well as we did.]
[Heejin: I think that's possible, you know?]

685
00:34:38,540 --> 00:34:40,150
[Hyeyeon: No way, seriously.
Though I can't guarantee it!]

686
00:34:40,150 --> 00:34:42,010
[Hyeyeon: Though I can't guarantee it!]

687
00:34:42,010 --> 00:34:44,679
[Hyeyeon: But it's highly unlikely.]

688
00:34:44,219 --> 00:34:44,820
Seriously.

689
00:34:44,679 --> 00:34:47,889
[Hyeyeon: I am so glad
you're the one sitting next to me.]

690
00:34:47,889 --> 00:34:48,960
[Hyeyeon: I'm so happy.]

691
00:34:48,960 --> 00:34:52,159
[Hyeyeon: Honestly, I checked the time
a few times on the way.]

692
00:34:52,159 --> 00:34:55,090
[Hyeyeon: And every time I checked,
time had flown by.]

693
00:34:53,820 --> 00:34:54,580
Really?

694
00:34:54,580 --> 00:34:56,940
That's why I think it's so great.

695
00:34:55,630 --> 00:34:56,960
[Hyeyeon: It's so nice.]

696
00:34:56,960 --> 00:35:01,770
[Hyeyeon: You really have to click.]

697
00:35:02,300 --> 00:35:06,840
[Through the V.I.B.E match, Hyeyeon & Heejin
wrap up their first meeting]

698
00:35:09,240 --> 00:35:14,310
[They discovered they had so much in common]

699
00:35:15,650 --> 00:35:21,250
[What kind of feelings did this first meeting
spark in their hearts?]

700
00:35:25,490 --> 00:35:27,560
[Please head to the gathering spot, BI-LIVE]

701
00:35:28,190 --> 00:35:31,130
[Yongkyu: Shall we head to the car?]
[Sujin: Sure, let's go.]

702
00:35:31,130 --> 00:35:33,800
[Yongkyu: Looks like you have a lot of stuff.
I'll carry it for you.]
[Sujin: Oh, thank you.]

703
00:35:33,800 --> 00:35:35,670
[Sujin: It's super heavy though,
you sure you're good?]

704
00:35:36,220 --> 00:35:36,780
Is it that heavy?

705
00:35:36,470 --> 00:35:38,340
[Sujin: It basically weighs as much as I do...]

706
00:35:38,340 --> 00:35:39,940
[Sujin: Thank you.]

707
00:35:40,210 --> 00:35:42,880
[Yongkyu: You're not trying to run away
with all this luggage, right?]
[Sujin: No way!]

708
00:35:43,680 --> 00:35:47,680
[Yongkyu: This is so much stuff.
It's like you're moving abroad.]

709
00:35:47,680 --> 00:35:49,820
[Sujin: More like moving houses, right?]

710
00:35:49,820 --> 00:35:51,680
[Yongkyu: Exactly.]

711
00:35:59,430 --> 00:36:02,360
[Yongkyu: You must be starving, right?
Sujin: Yeah.]

712
00:36:03,280 --> 00:36:05,200
[Sneakily]

713
00:36:04,740 --> 00:36:05,940
Have one.

714
00:36:05,300 --> 00:36:09,300
[Sujin: Oh, Ferrero Rocher!]

715
00:36:09,300 --> 00:36:12,240
[Sujin: Thank you so much.]

716
00:36:13,040 --> 00:36:14,910
[Yongkyu: I saved it just for this.]

717
00:36:14,910 --> 00:36:17,310
[Sujin: For me?]

718
00:36:16,140 --> 00:36:16,860
Yep.

719
00:36:18,380 --> 00:36:22,110
[Sujin: He is so sweet and gentlemanly.
It completely relaxes the vibe.]

720
00:36:22,650 --> 00:36:27,720
[Sujin: It really eased a lot of my nerves.]

721
00:36:30,120 --> 00:36:32,790
[Yongkyu: Oh, by the way,
I haven't even asked your name yet.]

722
00:36:32,790 --> 00:36:34,390
[Yongkyu: What's your name?]

723
00:36:35,460 --> 00:36:38,130
[Sujin: I'm Sujin. Sujin.]

724
00:36:38,130 --> 00:36:39,730
[Yongkyu: And your last name?]

725
00:36:39,730 --> 00:36:42,130
[Sujin: My last name is Go!]

726
00:36:42,130 --> 00:36:44,800
[Yongkyu: Go Sujin... Sujin?]
[Sujin: Yes, Go Sujin.]

727
00:36:45,340 --> 00:36:46,940
[Yongkyu: I'm Koo Yongkyu.]

728
00:36:46,820 --> 00:36:48,900
-Koo Yongkyu. -Koo Yongkyu.

729
00:36:46,940 --> 00:36:49,080
[Sujin: Koo Yongkyu!]

730
00:36:49,080 --> 00:36:49,900
[Yongkyu: A bit of a tongue twister, right?]

731
00:36:49,900 --> 00:36:52,280
[Sujin: Koo Yongkyu.]

732
00:36:49,900 --> 00:36:52,220
-Koo Yongkyu. -Yongkyu.

733
00:36:52,280 --> 00:36:53,610
[Sujin: Yeah, it is a bit tricky.]

734
00:36:55,210 --> 00:36:57,080
[Sujin: It's a little hard to say, but it's fine!]

735
00:36:57,880 --> 00:37:01,350
[Yongkyu: The name Yongkyu is just kind
of tricky to pronounce.]

736
00:37:01,420 --> 00:37:04,500
-Yongkyu, Yongkyu, Yongkyu. -Yongkyu, Yongkyu.

737
00:37:01,890 --> 00:37:06,160
[Sujin is practicing her pronunciation]

738
00:37:05,700 --> 00:37:06,380
Yongkyu.

739
00:37:06,160 --> 00:37:09,630
[Sujin: Just the name is fine,
but adding the last name...]

740
00:37:08,300 --> 00:37:08,700
Yeah.

741
00:37:09,630 --> 00:37:13,630
[Yongkyu: Ah, adding the "Koo"?]
[Sujin: Yeah, with the last name,
it gets a bit tricky.]

742
00:37:15,770 --> 00:37:19,240
[Sujin: It's kind of like a tongue twister, right?]
[Hahaha.]

743
00:37:19,240 --> 00:37:23,780
[Yongkyu: Honestly, I've never seen
anyone get it right on the first try.]

744
00:37:24,540 --> 00:37:26,180
Whenever I tell people my name...

745
00:37:26,180 --> 00:37:28,310
[Yongkyu: Wow, this is gorgeous!]

746
00:37:28,850 --> 00:37:32,050
[Sujin: Yeah, this totally feels like
a scenic driving route, right?]
[Yongkyu: Totally.]

747
00:37:32,480 --> 00:37:35,250
[They speed along with a breathtaking ocean view]

748
00:37:34,500 --> 00:37:35,520
The color is so beautiful.

749
00:37:35,520 --> 00:37:37,660
[Sujin: Want to roll down the windows a bit?
Yongkyu: Oh, sure!]

750
00:37:38,720 --> 00:37:41,130
[Yongkyu: Let's catch some breeze.]

751
00:37:41,390 --> 00:37:44,330
[Sujin: Once the windows were down,
the view got even better.]

752
00:37:44,600 --> 00:37:47,800
[Sujin: I asked him, "Should we open the windows?"]

753
00:37:47,800 --> 00:37:51,540
[Sujin: And right then, he goes, "Oh, sure!"
and we just let the wind hit us.]

754
00:37:51,540 --> 00:37:56,080
[Sujin: Staring at that beautiful ocean together—
that moment really stuck with me.]

755
00:37:56,080 --> 00:37:59,550
[Sujin: He gives off this really gentle energy.
Warm and comforting?]

756
00:38:00,610 --> 00:38:02,480
[Yongkyu: What's your MBTI?]

757
00:38:02,480 --> 00:38:03,820
[Sujin: Take a guess.]

758
00:38:03,820 --> 00:38:06,220
[Sujin: What do you think my MBTI is?]

759
00:38:06,490 --> 00:38:11,290
[Yongkyu: Well, the first letter
is definitely E.]

760
00:38:11,290 --> 00:38:12,890
[Yongkyu: And then...]

761
00:38:12,890 --> 00:38:15,030
[Yongkyu: Is it S?]

762
00:38:15,030 --> 00:38:20,370
[Sujin: Hey, I asked you to guess.
Why are you asking me?]
[Yongkyu: Not S?]

763
00:38:19,100 --> 00:38:19,780
Not S?

764
00:38:21,060 --> 00:38:23,540
[Yongkyu: EN...]

765
00:38:23,540 --> 00:38:25,300
[Yongkyu: EN... T...]

766
00:38:25,300 --> 00:38:26,300
[Yongkyu: EN... T... J.]

767
00:38:26,420 --> 00:38:27,700
[Wrong.]

768
00:38:27,700 --> 00:38:29,460
[Yongkyu: Did I miss all the last letters?]

769
00:38:29,460 --> 00:38:33,580
[Sujin: Not all of them. N and T are right.]

770
00:38:34,340 --> 00:38:37,720
[Yongkyu: Are you an INTP?
Sujin: Yep.]

771
00:38:37,720 --> 00:38:39,850
[Sujin: I don't really seem like an INTP, do I?]

772
00:38:39,850 --> 00:38:41,450
[Yongkyu: Yeah, honestly, not at all.]

773
00:38:41,450 --> 00:38:46,260
[Sujin: Everyone says
I seem like an ENFP or ENTP.]

774
00:38:47,060 --> 00:38:51,060
[Yongkyu: I actually know
INTPs pretty well.]

775
00:38:51,060 --> 00:38:53,470
[Sujin: Oh, really? Why's that?]

776
00:38:53,470 --> 00:38:55,870
[Yongkyu: They kind of have... well...]

777
00:38:55,870 --> 00:38:58,270
[Yongkyu: their own thing.]

778
00:38:58,270 --> 00:39:02,010
[Yongkyu: They're often hard to reach.]

779
00:39:01,300 --> 00:39:02,020
A little bit.

780
00:39:02,010 --> 00:39:03,880
[Sujin: Really? Hard to reach?]

781
00:39:03,880 --> 00:39:06,550
[Yongkyu: Yes.]
[Sujin: But I'm not that hard to reach.]

782
00:39:06,550 --> 00:39:10,020
[Sujin: What counts as hard to reach?]

783
00:39:10,020 --> 00:39:11,620
[Yongkyu: What counts as hard to reach?]

784
00:39:11,020 --> 00:39:11,460
Yeah.

785
00:39:11,620 --> 00:39:14,550
[Sujin: Like, for me, if someone doesn't
reply for 3 hours, that's a bit hard to accept.]

786
00:39:14,550 --> 00:39:17,220
[Yongkyu: I feel like the standard changes
depending on what they're doing.]

787
00:39:17,220 --> 00:39:19,090
[Yongkyu: If it's between people in a relationship,]

788
00:39:19,420 --> 00:39:21,760
[Yongkyu: if they're at work, I don't mind
however long it takes to reply.]

789
00:39:21,760 --> 00:39:23,020
[Yongkyu: If they're busy, they're busy.]

790
00:39:22,820 --> 00:39:23,260
True.

791
00:39:23,020 --> 00:39:24,160
[Yongkyu: But if it's not work hours,]

792
00:39:24,160 --> 00:39:28,700
[Yongkyu: like on a day off
or after work,]

793
00:39:28,700 --> 00:39:31,100
[Yongkyu: they don't have to reply instantly,]

794
00:39:31,100 --> 00:39:34,840
[Yongkyu: but there should still
be some kind of response.]

795
00:39:35,910 --> 00:39:39,380
[Yongkyu: You don't really look
at your phone much, do you?]

796
00:39:39,380 --> 00:39:40,980
[Sujin: I do...]

797
00:39:40,980 --> 00:39:43,120
[Yongkyu: You ignore
your Kakaotalk messages, right?]

798
00:39:43,120 --> 00:39:45,250
[Sujin: Well, when I get home]

799
00:39:45,250 --> 00:39:47,650
[Sujin: and focus on doing something—]

800
00:39:47,650 --> 00:39:52,220
[Sujin: for example, if I want something to eat,
I have to cook it myself.]

801
00:39:51,740 --> 00:39:52,340
Right.

802
00:39:52,220 --> 00:39:53,340
[Sujin: Then I have to look up a recipe, right?]

803
00:39:53,340 --> 00:39:55,900
[Sujin: While I'm checking a recipe,
people obviously can't reach me.]

804
00:39:53,500 --> 00:39:53,860
Yeah.

805
00:39:55,900 --> 00:39:57,530
[Sujin: That's the kind of time
when I'm hard to reach.]

806
00:39:58,300 --> 00:39:59,540
[Sujin: If someone asks me,
"Why were you not replying?"]

807
00:39:59,540 --> 00:40:02,620
[Sujin: I'll be like, "Oh, I was doing this!"]

808
00:40:02,620 --> 00:40:04,860
[Yongkyu: If it's a reason like that,
of course it's fine.]

809
00:40:04,860 --> 00:40:09,940
[Yongkyu: But there are people who literally just
don't check their notifications at all.]

810
00:40:09,940 --> 00:40:11,270
[Sujin: I'm not that type.]

811
00:40:11,270 --> 00:40:13,940
[Sujin: I don't deliberately ignore messages.]

812
00:40:11,420 --> 00:40:12,150
It's just...

813
00:40:14,980 --> 00:40:16,380
[Giggles]

814
00:40:16,440 --> 00:40:18,840
[Sujin: Looks like you've been through it.]

815
00:40:18,840 --> 00:40:23,120
[Sujin: Did an INTP
break your heart or something?]

816
00:40:25,820 --> 00:40:29,700
[Sujin: Oh, we have a new mission.]

817
00:40:26,500 --> 00:40:27,140
Yeah.

818
00:40:29,700 --> 00:40:31,120
[Sujin: Let me read it.]

819
00:40:32,190 --> 00:40:35,660
[Sujin: The first date on Stand BI Me
is a 1-on-1 date.]

820
00:40:35,660 --> 00:40:40,200
[Sujin: Your were matched
by AI based on your V.I.B.E. test.]

821
00:40:41,370 --> 00:40:51,940
[The AI match analysis
for Go Sujin & Koo Yongkyu is:
"Quietly seeping in, becoming an irresistible bond
before you even realize it."]

822
00:40:57,700 --> 00:40:59,580
[Sujin: Oh, so everyone else]

823
00:40:59,580 --> 00:41:03,260
[Sujin: got matched based on that test, too.]

824
00:41:03,260 --> 00:41:04,590
[Yongkyu: Looks like it.]

825
00:41:04,590 --> 00:41:08,060
[Yongkyu: I totally thought
we'd all meet as a group first.]

826
00:41:08,060 --> 00:41:08,860
[Sujin: Me too.]

827
00:41:08,860 --> 00:41:12,870
[Sujin: I thought they'd have us pick
our NO.1 first impression,]

828
00:41:12,870 --> 00:41:15,530
[Sujin: something like that.]

829
00:41:16,340 --> 00:41:22,210
[Sujin: Since it was our first time meeting,
it could've been so awkward.]

830
00:41:20,220 --> 00:41:22,980
But he made the whole vibe so smooth.

831
00:41:22,210 --> 00:41:25,950
[Sujin: “Quietly seeping in”
was kind of an accurate description.]

832
00:41:27,810 --> 00:41:30,480
[Yongkyu: But don't INTPs usually have, like...]

833
00:41:30,480 --> 00:41:34,220
[Yongkyu: a specific type?]

834
00:41:34,220 --> 00:41:41,160
[Sujin: Oh, specific... yeah, we have]

835
00:41:41,160 --> 00:41:43,830
[Sujin: our own private standards.]

836
00:41:43,830 --> 00:41:47,570
[Sujin: The question is
whether someone can meet those standards.]

837
00:41:47,570 --> 00:41:51,570
[Yongkyu: I heard you can tell at first glance?]

838
00:41:51,570 --> 00:41:53,710
[Yongkyu: Kind of like falling hard right away...]

839
00:41:54,770 --> 00:41:55,970
[Sujin: Falling hard right away?]

840
00:41:55,970 --> 00:41:58,240
[Sujin: Am I the type to fall hard right away?]

841
00:41:58,510 --> 00:42:00,980
[Sujin: I used to be like that.]

842
00:42:00,980 --> 00:42:06,620
[Sujin: But now, I want to take my time
and see how things go before deciding.]

843
00:42:10,040 --> 00:42:14,040
[Yongkyu: What's the longest relationship
you've had?]

844
00:42:15,110 --> 00:42:19,110
[Sujin: Under 2 years.]
[Yongkyu: 2 years?]

845
00:42:20,180 --> 00:42:23,020
[Sujin: What's your longest?]

846
00:42:23,020 --> 00:42:26,220
[Yongkyu: For me...]
[Sujin: Don't tell me like 8 years.]

847
00:42:28,760 --> 00:42:32,420
[Yongkyu: Around that, actually.]

848
00:42:32,420 --> 00:42:33,300
[Yongkyu: Years...]
[Sujin: 8 years?]

849
00:42:33,300 --> 00:42:37,300
[Sujin: You dated one person for 8 years?]
[Yongkyu: Yeah.]

850
00:42:37,840 --> 00:42:39,970
[Sujin: Didn't you ever
hit a rut in the relationship?]

851
00:42:40,540 --> 00:42:42,640
[Yongkyu: No, we didn't really have that.]

852
00:42:42,640 --> 00:42:45,310
[Yongkyu: I mean, I do have to
really like the person]

853
00:42:45,310 --> 00:42:47,710
[Yongkyu: to date them that long.]

854
00:42:47,710 --> 00:42:50,120
[Yongkyu: But they also have to
really like me just as much]

855
00:42:50,120 --> 00:42:52,250
[Yongkyu: for that to be possible.]

856
00:42:52,520 --> 00:42:57,320
[Yongkyu: Because I tend
to go for longterm relationships,]

857
00:42:57,320 --> 00:43:05,330
[Yongkyu: I think about a lot of things
before starting one.]

858
00:43:07,470 --> 00:43:09,600
[Sujin: Considering things like]

859
00:43:09,600 --> 00:43:12,540
[Sujin: personality and other aspects,
what makes you think,]

860
00:43:12,540 --> 00:43:16,010
[Sujin: “This is someone
I could date for a long time”?]

861
00:43:16,010 --> 00:43:19,210
[Yongkyu: Shared topics? Sense of humor?]

862
00:43:19,480 --> 00:43:21,220
[Yongkyu: Having the same sense of humor.]

863
00:43:21,220 --> 00:43:26,950
[Yongkyu: Someone who can laugh
and cry over the same things as me
is the kind of person I can date the longest.]

864
00:43:30,690 --> 00:43:37,630
[Sujin: For you to last 8 years,
they must have been your soulmate.]

865
00:43:37,900 --> 00:43:42,700
[Sujin: You must've been a perfect match.]
[Yongkyu: Yeah, we were together a long time.]

866
00:43:44,300 --> 00:43:46,970
[Sujin: Overall, I was happy with the date.]

867
00:43:46,970 --> 00:43:49,110
[Sujin: Chatting with him was fun.]

868
00:43:49,110 --> 00:43:50,980
[Sujin: We talked about everything.]

869
00:43:50,980 --> 00:43:52,310
[Sujin: And he's a great listener.]

870
00:43:52,310 --> 00:43:56,050
[Sujin: Actually, I guess I didn't ask him much.]

871
00:43:56,580 --> 00:44:00,590
[Sujin: I wasn't into him at first,]

872
00:44:00,590 --> 00:44:03,260
[Sujin: but I got a bit closer to him.]

873
00:44:03,520 --> 00:44:08,590
[Yongkyu: It was fun driving along the coast.
It's been a while.]

874
00:44:08,590 --> 00:44:12,600
[Yongkyu: I saw her more proactive side,]

875
00:44:12,870 --> 00:44:15,270
[Yongkyu: and she actually made up]

876
00:44:15,270 --> 00:44:17,400
[Yongkyu: some of my own shortcomings.]

877
00:44:17,400 --> 00:44:19,810
[Yongkyu: I did think that at some point.]

878
00:44:19,810 --> 00:44:22,740
[Yongkyu: A bit of pressure?
I felt that a little.]

879
00:44:22,740 --> 00:44:25,950
[Yongkyu: But maybe I'm
just being hard on myself.]

880
00:44:26,480 --> 00:44:31,550
[Can they become a relationship
that quietly seeps in?]

881
00:44:34,920 --> 00:44:37,590
[Jinwoo: Aren't you hungry?]
[Just a little bit, haha.]

882
00:44:36,740 --> 00:44:37,500
Right?

883
00:44:37,860 --> 00:44:39,460
[Seungho: Well...]
[Jinwoo: Well...]

884
00:44:39,460 --> 00:44:41,600
[Jinwoo: What the, in unison? Haha.]

885
00:44:41,600 --> 00:44:44,270
[Seungho: But I did just have some lemonade.]

886
00:44:44,270 --> 00:44:46,140
[Jinwoo: I had an iced americano, too.]

887
00:44:45,620 --> 00:44:46,280
Seriously?

888
00:44:46,940 --> 00:44:48,270
[Seungho: I'm not really a coffee person...]

889
00:44:48,270 --> 00:44:49,340
[Jinwoo: Oh, you can't do coffee?]

890
00:44:49,340 --> 00:44:50,140
[Jinwoo: The caffeine...]

891
00:44:50,140 --> 00:44:51,470
[Seungho: It's not that I can't.]

892
00:44:51,470 --> 00:44:53,610
[Seungho: I just don't like it.]

893
00:44:53,610 --> 00:44:55,740
[Jinwoo: You don't like coffee?]

894
00:44:55,740 --> 00:44:58,410
[Seungho: I'd much rather
have something sweet...]

895
00:44:57,180 --> 00:44:58,410
-Something sweet? -Yeah.

896
00:44:58,410 --> 00:45:00,280
[Jinwoo: Do you like juice then?]

897
00:45:00,280 --> 00:45:02,150
